To kill the way
this unsub does.

07:39.900 --> 07:40.700
Hey, guys.

07:53.100 --> 07:53.900
Over here.

07:54.900 --> 07:56.000
Someone was living here.

07:58.900 --> 08:00.000
There, you got
a dirty blanket,

08:00.000 --> 08:01.700
Hamburger wrappers,
and soda cans.

08:03.200 --> 08:05.200
Those kids weren't
the only ones here last night.

08:10.600 --> 08:11.700
What's that ? 

08:11.900 --> 08:14.100
One of the detectives' wives
made us cookies.

08:14.900 --> 08:16.800
Wow. Homemade cookies ? 

08:16.800 --> 08:20.100
Yeah, I guess that's what
they mean by southern hospitality.

08:20.100 --> 08:21.000
What are you saying ? 

08:21.000 --> 08:22.600
Southern hospitality ! 

08:22.600 --> 08:23.600
I need to concentrate...

08:25.000 --> 08:27.300
How can anybody hear
with all this work going on ? 

08:27.500 --> 08:29.100
Well, you're gonna
have to get used to it.

08:29.100 --> 08:30.700
Construction crews
are working around the clock.

08:31.000 --> 08:32.000
Saw it on the way in.

08:32.500 --> 08:34.400
City's trying to return
to its splendor,

08:34.400 --> 08:36.100
And that means that
houston's poorest

08:36.100 --> 08:37.500
Are being kicked out
of their homes.

08:39.700 --> 08:40.900
Unsub might be homeless.

08:41.799 --> 08:43.200
Appears to have been
living in a building

08:43.400 --> 08:45.600
Next to where the security
guard was attacked.

08:45.600 --> 08:48.400
These are the locations of the last
3 murders, all near abandoned buildings.

08:48.500 --> 08:50.800
I noticed the neighborhood.
Maybe he was recently displaced.

08:51.000 --> 08:52.300
Could be a motive.

08:52.500 --> 08:55.200
Construction worker,
security guard at a construction site.

08:55.400 --> 08:56.200
Payback ? 

08:56.200 --> 08:57.100
What about the homeless man ? 

08:57.100 --> 08:59.100
We get a lot of beefs down
there among the homeless.

