The trash is pretty much
cleared away.

12:45.500 --> 12:46.900
Yeah, i got a dirty blanket...

12:48.900 --> 12:50.700
Something else rolled up
in the corner.

12:51.800 --> 12:54.000
It's obvious he made himself
a place to sleep, but...

12:55.000 --> 12:56.200
He cleared it all away.

12:59.500 --> 13:01.300
It looks a lot like
the last place he was in.

13:01.600 --> 13:02.400
Huh.

13:03.200 --> 13:04.600
A new temporary home.

13:12.500 --> 13:14.200
Guys, it looks like
the jackhammer

13:14.200 --> 13:15.800
Must have knocked
some of the ceiling loose.

13:16.700 --> 13:19.200
It fell down all around him.
I'd be pretty scared, too.

13:19.700 --> 13:20.800
It's about survival.

13:22.400 --> 13:23.800
Carved out a place of his own,

13:23.800 --> 13:25.000
Saw a threat, he attacked.

13:26.300 --> 13:27.900
That's got to be why
the victims were so random.

13:28.700 --> 13:30.100
He didn't have
a relationship with them.

13:30.500 --> 13:32.100
They just happened to be
intruding on his home.

13:33.500 --> 13:35.100
We'll need to see
the other crime scenes.

13:35.100 --> 13:36.400
Sure ! Let's go ! 

13:38.100 --> 13:38.900
You all right ? 

13:38.900 --> 13:40.300
Yeah. You owe me.

13:47.600 --> 13:49.200
You all are looking
for someone in charge ? 

13:49.200 --> 13:50.700
I'm angie, one of
the administrators.

13:50.700 --> 13:52.900
Hi. I'm Agent Prentiss.
This is Agent Reid.

13:52.900 --> 13:54.000
We're with the fbi.

13:54.600 --> 13:55.800
Really ? 
Really.

13:57.300 --> 13:58.600
It looks like
you have your hands full.

13:59.000 --> 14:01.400
With the demolitions in the projects
and the abandoned buildings,

14:01.400 --> 14:03.100
There's no place else
for people to sleep.

14:03.100 --> 14:05.300
Well, thank god there are people
like you who take the time...

14:05.300 --> 14:06.700
Do you have a list of everyone
who comes through here ? 

14:06.700 --> 14:08.000
Angie: uh, we have
a sign-In sheet,

14:08.000 --> 14:10.100
But we don't force
anyone to sign if they don't want to.

14:10.100 --> 14:12.200
Some who do don't even
use their real names.

14:12.500 --> 14:14.100
Elvis eats here a lot.

14:14.300 --> 14:15.900
We would appreciate
any lists you have.

14:16.300 --> 14:17.100
Why ? 

14:17.100 --> 14:18.400
Have you noticed anyone who acts

14:18.400 --> 14:20.600
Unusually aggressive
towards the other residents ? 

14:20.900 --> 14:21.800
What's this about ? 

14:21.800 --> 14:23.700
A series of murders in the area.

14:23.700 --> 14:25.700
The perpetrator
may be a homeless man.

14:25.700 --> 14:27.100
Maybe someone who stays here.

14:27.100 --> 14:29.100
He may even be in this room
as we speak.

14:29.100 --> 14:30.300
My god, Reid.

14:30.300 --> 14:32.700
Have you noticed anyone
who acts paranoid or displays

14:32.700 --> 14:35.100
Explosive, unprovoked
bursts of violence,

14:35.100 --> 14:36.300
More than just
pushing and shoving ? 

14:36.300 --> 14:38.600
I mean, someone who really
tries to harm others.

14:38.600 --> 14:41.700
There are territorial fights
over food and places to sleep.

14:42.000 --> 14:44.300
The nurse treats people
for minor injuries all the time,

14:44.300 --> 14:46.000
But no one's seriously hurt.

14:46.200 --> 14:49.800
If anyone does come to mind,
give us a call.

14:49.800 --> 14:50.600
Thank you.

14:54.000 --> 14:55.000
A murderer ? 

14:55.000 --> 14:57.100
I'm sorry. Uh--Um...

14:58.200 --> 14:59.700
This investigation is still...

15:00.200 --> 15:02.600
No one's actually
been hurt in a shelter.

15:03.000 --> 15:05.300
We're just... We're acting with
an abundance of caution.

15:05.900 --> 15:07.700
So, please, let the police know

15:07.700 --> 15:09.100
If anything unusual occurs.

15:10.300 --> 15:11.200
Thanks.

15:20.300 --> 15:23.000
There's a high presence
of mental disorders with the homeless.

15:23.100 --> 15:23.900
Yeah.

15:24.200 --> 15:25.600
What the hell
was that in there ? 

15:25.600 --> 15:26.300
What ? 

15:26.300 --> 15:28.700
"He may even be in this room as we speak" ? 

15:28.700 --> 15:30.300
We have nothing to support that.

15:30.300 --> 15:32.200
We're investigating
a serial homicide.

15:32.200 --> 15:33.800
Should i have pretended
there's no danger ? 

15:33.800 --> 15:36.400
We just left that woman
potentially afraid

15:36.400 --> 15:38.300
Of every man who walks
into this shelter.

15:38.300 --> 15:40.900
Again, until we find
this unsub, how is that a bad thing ? 

15:42.200 --> 15:43.500
What is the matter with you ? 

