But then he stopped...

18:28.900 --> 18:30.400
And he looked at me funny.

18:32.700 --> 18:34.000
What do you mean by "funny" ? 

18:35.800 --> 18:37.200
He looked...

18:38.000 --> 18:39.100
Sad.

18:42.900 --> 18:44.400
He did say something.

18:45.300 --> 18:46.700
Not to my papa.

18:46.700 --> 18:47.900
To me.

18:49.000 --> 18:49.900
What was it ? 

18:51.600 --> 18:53.000
He said...

18:53.600 --> 18:54.700
Are you ok ? 

18:55.300 --> 18:56.300
Why are you crying ? 

18:56.300 --> 18:59.400
And then we ran.
Go away !  Go away ! 

19:10.500 --> 19:11.300
Maria...

19:13.600 --> 19:15.200
What you did was very brave.

19:17.900 --> 19:19.600
Can you help us
with one more thing ? 

19:19.600 --> 19:21.400
Can you tell us
what the man looked like ? 

19:23.500 --> 19:24.800
He was white.

19:25.900 --> 19:27.000
And tall.

19:27.800 --> 19:28.800
And dirty.

19:33.100 --> 19:35.300
And he had a ring like yours.

19:35.300 --> 19:36.300
Like that ? 

19:39.900 --> 19:41.300
I remember his ring.

19:42.800 --> 19:43.700
Thank you.

19:47.600 --> 19:48.800
Iabuela ! 

19:58.300 --> 19:59.200
Gracias.

20:04.700 --> 20:06.900
He asked if she was ok
and why was she crying.

20:06.900 --> 20:09.100
He wasn't aware of what
he was doing to her.

20:09.500 --> 20:10.700
Garcia's on line one.

20:11.500 --> 20:12.800
Go ahead, Penelope.

20:13.400 --> 20:14.900
All right, cowgirls and boys.

20:14.900 --> 20:15.700
Hey.

20:15.700 --> 20:17.500
I've got the comparison
satellite images

20:17.500 --> 20:19.500
Of the before-And-After
pictures, and i found something.

20:19.500 --> 20:20.300
Check it.

20:21.100 --> 20:21.900
Do you see it yet ? 

20:22.100 --> 20:22.900
Yeah.

20:23.100 --> 20:24.100
Yeah, an s.O.S.

20:24.600 --> 20:27.000
Yeah, it's made of debris
and other rocky bits of gobbledygook.

20:27.000 --> 20:28.900
This is the building
where the security guard got killed.

20:29.500 --> 20:30.700
He's asking for help.

20:31.100 --> 20:32.400
Wait, guys. Listen outside.

20:35.700 --> 20:38.300
Chaos. S.O.S.

20:38.800 --> 20:40.200
He's a war veteran.

20:41.500 --> 20:42.900
He thinks he's in a war zone.

20:44.700 --> 20:47.200
He left a distress signal
on the roof of one of the buildings.

20:47.700 --> 20:50.400
The quick strikes
are consistent with trained military

20:50.900 --> 20:52.000
He must have served in a place

20:52.000 --> 20:53.500
That looked or sounded like this ward.

20:53.900 --> 20:55.900
Well, we were right
about him being homeless, in a sense.

20:56.700 --> 20:59.500
Wherever he is, in his mental state,
he's certainly not at home.

20:59.500 --> 21:01.600
He may not even be aware
he's killing.

21:01.600 --> 21:02.700
Now, how's that ? 

21:02.800 --> 21:04.600
When soldiers suffered
from anxiety, depression,

21:04.600 --> 21:07.000
And flashbacks in world war i,
it was called shell shock.

21:07.000 --> 21:09.000
In world war ii,
battle fatigue.

21:09.000 --> 21:10.900
Now we refer to it as ptsd,

21:10.900 --> 21:12.900
Post-Traumatic
stress disorder, war related.

21:12.900 --> 21:15.900
A side effect of which
is slipping into dissociative states.

21:16.200 --> 21:18.200
The mind divorces itself
from reality

21:18.200 --> 21:19.900
So it can cope
with the trauma.

21:19.900 --> 21:21.300
He's reliving a memory.

21:21.300 --> 21:23.400
He's trapped in his head
in some war zone.

21:23.400 --> 21:25.500
Hiding and defending himself
from the enemy.

21:26.100 --> 21:29.200
Ok, so how do we find
a man who's trapped inside his head ? 

21:29.200 --> 21:30.300
He's got a wedding ring.

21:30.700 --> 21:31.800
Someone's missing him.

21:32.100 --> 21:34.400
Good. I'm with detective Fuller.

21:34.400 --> 21:36.500
Morgan has last crime scene to check.

21:36.800 --> 21:38.600
J.J., check
missing persons reports,

21:38.600 --> 21:40.300
See if anyone matches
the description.

21:40.300 --> 21:41.500
It would have been
filed recently,

21:41.500 --> 21:43.100
The last 2 or 3 days.
Ok.

21:43.100 --> 21:44.000
Thanks.

22:08.000 --> 22:08.900
Hey.

22:09.600 --> 22:10.900
You shouldn't be out here.

22:11.400 --> 22:12.600
It isn't safe.

22:17.800 --> 22:18.900
It isn't safe.

22:35.000 --> 22:38.600
Dana Woodridge and Max Weston...
Her husband and his best friend.

22:38.600 --> 22:41.100
Roy Woodridge
has been missing since tuesday.

22:42.500 --> 22:44.300
He was on his way home from work.

22:45.100 --> 22:46.800
He called before
he left the office

22:46.800 --> 22:50.400
And said we needed to talk
when he got home.

22:51.900 --> 22:53.400
He sounded upset.

22:55.400 --> 22:57.200
That was the last
I heard from him.

22:57.500 --> 22:59.300
What was he upset about ? 

23:00.400 --> 23:01.600
He didn't say.

23:02.200 --> 23:04.000
Dana called me that night

23:04.000 --> 23:05.500
When Roy didn't show up.

23:05.900 --> 23:06.700
So...

23:07.200 --> 23:09.800
The next morning we filed
a missing persons report.

23:10.400 --> 23:12.400
Mrs. Woodridge, where
does your husband work ? 

23:13.300 --> 23:16.000
He's a consultant
at a security firm downtown.

23:16.500 --> 23:18.800
Did your husband
ever serve in combat ? 

23:18.800 --> 23:19.700
Excuse me ? 

23:20.200 --> 23:21.500
Is he a war veteran ? 

23:23.700 --> 23:24.800
Yeah.
Uh...

23:24.800 --> 23:25.700
We both are.

23:25.700 --> 23:27.100
We were in
special ops.

23:27.100 --> 23:28.500
75th ranger regiment,

23:28.500 --> 23:30.400
Bravo company, 3rd battalion.

23:31.500 --> 23:32.700
But Roy...

23:33.200 --> 23:36.600
He retired shortly after
things went bad in Mogadishu.

23:36.700 --> 23:38.400
That was back in 1993.

23:38.700 --> 23:41.400
Let me ask you this... Does he display
any sort of, uh...

23:41.700 --> 23:44.000
Behavioral tics...
Certain everyday things,

23:44.000 --> 23:46.000
They make him jumpy or startled ? 

23:46.600 --> 23:47.400
Why ? 

23:48.500 --> 23:49.500
Does he ? 

23:49.800 --> 23:51.800
Is this going to help find him ? 

23:52.100 --> 23:53.800
Mrs. Woodridge, please.

23:53.800 --> 23:56.200
We need to know everything
we can about your husband.

23:57.000 --> 24:00.000
We all had a...
hard time over there,

24:00.000 --> 24:02.900
You know... you bring
some things home with you.

24:03.500 --> 24:04.500
Like what ? 

24:07.000 --> 24:09.500
He has a hard time
with loud noises.

24:11.600 --> 24:13.200
He can't be in crowds.

24:15.100 --> 24:16.400
He has nightmares

24:16.400 --> 24:18.900
And wakes up in cold sweats.

24:21.700 --> 24:23.400
The smells are the worst.

24:23.800 --> 24:24.600
He...

24:25.400 --> 24:27.400
If he smells
something burning,

24:27.400 --> 24:30.800
Like a barbecue or gas or fire...

24:32.100 --> 24:33.300
He gets sick.

24:35.600 --> 24:38.400
It really only got bad
about a year ago.

24:39.900 --> 24:41.600
What happened to him in Somalia ? 

24:42.500 --> 24:43.400
Nothing.

24:45.900 --> 24:47.200
Combat happened.

24:49.500 --> 24:50.600
What does that mean ? 

24:56.800 --> 24:59.400
I'm gonna get a drink of water.

25:11.100 --> 25:14.300
You knew your friend
was suffering from symptoms of ptsd ? 

25:16.100 --> 25:17.700
He was a changed man, wasn't he ? 

25:18.700 --> 25:20.000
He was anxious,

25:20.700 --> 25:22.100
Paranoid, distant.

25:23.600 --> 25:25.000
He was far away in his head.

25:25.000 --> 25:27.600
I tried to get him
into a vet center to talk to somebody,

25:27.600 --> 25:29.000
But he said he was all right.

25:29.400 --> 25:30.800
What happened
in Somalia ? 

25:30.800 --> 25:32.000
What's he reliving ? 

25:36.500 --> 25:38.100
You can't tell Dana.

25:38.800 --> 25:40.500
Roy never wanted her to know.

25:44.000 --> 25:45.000
Thank you.

25:46.800 --> 25:49.100
Could somebody please
tell me what's going on ? 

25:49.500 --> 25:51.700
There have been some
people hurt recently,

25:51.700 --> 25:55.000
And we think that there
may be someone lost on the streets.

25:55.300 --> 25:57.400
Someone who thinks
that he's still at war.

25:58.100 --> 26:00.900
But Roy would never hurt
innocent people.

26:02.700 --> 26:04.900
Well, why would he even
be in this neighborhood ? 

26:07.100 --> 26:10.000
Hey, Garcia. We have
Mrs. Woodridge here with us.

26:10.400 --> 26:11.600
Oh, uh, well,

26:11.600 --> 26:14.300
I found an '02
white ford f150 pickup truck.

26:14.300 --> 26:16.300
Oh, my god. That's his truck.

26:16.300 --> 26:17.500
It was impounded.

26:17.500 --> 26:20.000
Uh, it had a flat tire
and was picked up on Lyon street

26:20.000 --> 26:22.100
About a quarter of a mile
from highway 59.

26:22.600 --> 26:25.100
He takes the east tex freeway
to work every day.

26:27.600 --> 26:29.400
Mrs. Woodridge,
I'm very sorry...

26:30.200 --> 26:32.200
But this is definitely
your husband.

26:33.200 --> 26:34.100
What  ? 

26:45.700 --> 26:46.800
Roy and I...

26:47.700 --> 26:51.100
We were escorting
a u.N. Aid caravan to a refugee camp.

26:52.000 --> 26:54.000
Our convoy was ambushed.

26:54.700 --> 26:56.200
The front received heavy fire,

26:56.200 --> 26:57.300
But we were in the rear,

26:57.300 --> 26:59.000
So we managed to escape.

27:00.500 --> 27:04.900
We hid for 2 days
in and out of abandoned buildings that...

27:04.900 --> 27:06.800
Insurgents were looking for us.

27:10.500 --> 27:13.300
One night I was sleeping,
Roy kept watch.

27:14.800 --> 27:17.700
When I woke up, there was
an ak-47 pointed right at me.

27:48.700 --> 27:49.800
A child.

27:51.000 --> 27:51.700
Yeah.

27:52.500 --> 27:54.500
They were all babies
back in Mogadishu,

27:54.500 --> 27:55.700
But this one...

27:56.000 --> 27:58.300
He couldn't have been
more than 11 or 12.

27:59.200 --> 28:00.400
Then what happened ? 

28:00.400 --> 28:02.500
We finally found a radio...

28:03.700 --> 28:05.900
Fixed it,
called for an extraction.

28:07.200 --> 28:09.100
Did you put out an S.O.S. ? 

28:10.000 --> 28:11.000
Yeah, we...

28:11.100 --> 28:14.100
We used rocks to put
an s.O.S. In the dirt

28:14.100 --> 28:15.900
So the blackhawks
could locate us.

28:15.900 --> 28:17.200
How did you know that ? 

28:18.300 --> 28:19.300
Look,

28:19.400 --> 28:21.900
If this is roy,
you're not gonna find him.

28:21.900 --> 28:23.500
He's trained and skilled
at survival.

28:23.500 --> 28:24.900
He knows how to hide.

28:25.300 --> 28:26.700
We think he has a gun.

28:29.000 --> 28:30.500
Well, he doesn't miss.

29:00.700 --> 29:02.200
We need to put
a s.W.A.T. Team together,

29:02.200 --> 29:04.000
Plan a grid search
and go building to building.

29:04.000 --> 29:05.600
He's reliving the war, isn't he ? 

29:05.600 --> 29:08.000
A specific incident
in which he killed a child.

29:08.300 --> 29:10.500
Guys, the s.W.A.T. Team's
gonna have guns, right ? 

29:10.800 --> 29:12.700
What happens if he tries
to fight them ? 

29:33.100 --> 29:35.200
Can I get you something,
Mrs. Woodridge ? 

29:35.200 --> 29:36.900
Those men are going
after Roy ? 

29:39.000 --> 29:40.400
Do they need so many guns ? 

29:40.400 --> 29:41.800
He's just one man.

29:41.800 --> 29:43.700
It... It's protocol, ma'am.

29:43.700 --> 29:45.200
How badly were they hurt ? 

29:47.100 --> 29:49.400
Y'all said
that people were hurt.

29:52.400 --> 29:54.000
Some people were murdered.

29:55.200 --> 29:56.200
Murdered ? 

30:01.400 --> 30:03.600
Mrs. Woodridge...
He never really came home.

30:06.400 --> 30:08.400
I lost him 14 years ago.

30:10.100 --> 30:12.100
It's been like
living with a ghost.

30:16.300 --> 30:17.300
Help him.

30:18.300 --> 30:19.600
Please, help him.

30:22.300 --> 30:24.000
We'll do everything we can.

30:24.800 --> 30:25.700
Ok ? 

30:31.600 --> 30:32.900
Reid, what are you working on ? 

30:33.400 --> 30:35.100
3 days ago police shut down
the freeway

30:35.100 --> 30:37.200
At 5 p.M. For 10 minutes.

30:38.100 --> 30:41.500
Cars were stalled and Roy must have
tried to exit on the surface streets.

30:42.000 --> 30:45.300
Sadly, he ended up in an unfamiliar
area with a flat tire.

30:45.600 --> 30:47.800
He was changing that tire
when an 8-Story building

30:47.800 --> 30:50.200
On market imploded
5 blocks away.

30:52.000 --> 30:53.900
He heard the explosion
and reacted

30:53.900 --> 30:55.900
Like a mortar bomb
had landed nearby.

30:56.500 --> 30:59.200
This explosion is what
triggered his dissociation.

30:59.200 --> 31:01.100
And since then,
he's been stuck in that state.

31:01.200 --> 31:03.400
Running when he needed to,
sleeping when he could,

31:03.400 --> 31:05.200
Camouflaging himself
into his surroundings,

31:05.200 --> 31:07.400
And hiding from
his perceived enemies.

31:11.300 --> 31:13.200
He's relieving
the worst moment of his life.

31:13.500 --> 31:14.900
He's gotta be
terrified.

31:15.000 --> 31:16.000
Yeah.

31:22.600 --> 31:23.600
Yeah, what do you have ? 

31:23.600 --> 31:25.000
Why isn't Derek
answering his phone ? 

31:25.100 --> 31:26.700
He's probably stuck
underground somewhere.

31:26.700 --> 31:27.600
Underground ? 

31:27.900 --> 31:29.200
I'll explain later.

31:29.200 --> 31:31.200
Oh. Ok. So,
I finally got through

31:31.200 --> 31:32.800
All those recent police reports
he asked me to check,

31:32.800 --> 31:34.800
Which, by the way,
it was no hopscotch through the park,

31:34.800 --> 31:36.000
Because that precinct you're at

31:36.000 --> 31:38.600
Is kind of tragically behind
on their paperwork.

31:38.600 --> 31:39.700
Yeah, they're undermanned.

31:39.700 --> 31:40.800
Oh, Jeez, really ? 

31:40.800 --> 31:42.300
I can't imagine
what that feels like.

31:42.400 --> 31:44.600
Oh, no, wait.
Yes, I can, 'cause...

31:44.600 --> 31:46.200
Garcia, do you have
anything for me ? 

31:46.600 --> 31:49.500
Well, he told me to look
for anything unusual,

31:49.500 --> 31:51.300
And it's all usual.

31:51.300 --> 31:53.800
Minor break-Ins,
apartment burglaries,

31:53.800 --> 31:56.500
Televisions, stereos,
car thefts, and smash and grabs.

31:56.500 --> 31:58.100
Common stuff in the world
of burgling.

31:58.100 --> 31:59.400
Nothing a guy
lost in the streets

31:59.400 --> 32:00.900
Might use for survival ? 

32:00.900 --> 32:02.400
No, nothing reported.

32:02.400 --> 32:04.200
It... like I said,
it's all petty.

32:04.200 --> 32:05.000
There's a...

32:05.100 --> 32:07.500
Some vandalism
at construction sites.

32:07.600 --> 32:09.300
Communications radio
missing from one of them.

32:09.300 --> 32:11.100
Wait... Did you say radio ? 

32:11.100 --> 32:13.500
Yeah. Construction Foreman
reported that one of their

32:13.500 --> 32:16.400
Trucks had been broken into
and a hand-Held radio was stolen.

32:16.700 --> 32:18.800
Yesterday.12 hours ago.

32:20.200 --> 32:21.400
Is that what you're looking for ? 

32:22.600 --> 32:23.400
Reid ? 

32:27.100 --> 32:28.200
This is Roy Woodridge,

32:28.200 --> 32:30.000
6'1", 195 pounds,

32:30.000 --> 32:31.000
44 years old.

32:31.700 --> 32:33.700
Brown hair,
former army ranger.

32:34.800 --> 32:37.000
It's imperative
you don't try to apprehend him alone.

32:37.500 --> 32:39.100
He won't understand
what's happening.

32:39.600 --> 32:41.400
He may try
to defend himself.

32:41.900 --> 32:44.300
He's armed, and he's an excellent
marksman.

32:45.000 --> 32:46.300
He may have stolen a radio,

32:46.300 --> 32:47.700
A walkie-Talkie.

32:51.200 --> 32:52.000
We were right.

32:52.000 --> 32:54.400
He had a nest of sorts
right near every murder scene.

32:54.500 --> 32:56.600
There was a burglary
of a two-Way radio

32:56.600 --> 32:58.400
From a construction site
recently.

32:58.400 --> 32:59.400
That could be Roy.

32:59.400 --> 33:01.300
We only used uhf
back then.

33:01.300 --> 33:02.500
He's looking for help.

33:03.000 --> 33:06.100
And he'll keep trying to
contact operations command.

33:06.200 --> 33:08.700
Detective, can we get a dozen uhf
radios set up in this room,

33:08.700 --> 33:11.700
And each of them tuned
to each of the preset channel frequencies ? 

33:11.700 --> 33:12.600
Right away.

33:12.600 --> 33:13.700
Wait a minute.

33:13.700 --> 33:15.600
When he calls,
we need to be very careful

33:15.600 --> 33:17.000
With the communication,

33:17.000 --> 33:19.900
Because we set up
specific responses to contact op com

33:19.900 --> 33:22.000
So we could avoid
hostile interception

33:22.000 --> 33:24.400
And to establish
"no danger" signals.

33:24.400 --> 33:27.800
And we had specific names
to identify our squad to the operator.

33:27.800 --> 33:29.500
Do you remember
the language you set up ? 

33:29.500 --> 33:30.700
I couldn't forget it.

33:30.800 --> 33:32.000
Roy and I wrote it.

33:32.000 --> 33:35.200
The callout was, "this is John Doe
looking for mark rippen."

33:35.200 --> 33:37.200
Rippen was our hero
at the time...

33:37.200 --> 33:40.200
Number 11, quarterback
for the redskins in 1993.

33:40.200 --> 33:41.600
Now we know where he is
in his head.

33:42.700 --> 33:44.600
He calls in, we'll be
on the other end when he does.

33:44.600 --> 33:45.900
What if he doesn't call ? 

33:46.200 --> 33:48.100
What if he just
kills someone else ? 

33:48.100 --> 33:50.000
Well, we'll deal
with that if it happens.

33:50.000 --> 33:51.700
Kind of easy for you to say.

33:51.700 --> 33:53.900
This guy may be messed up,
but that doesn't change the fact

33:53.900 --> 33:56.000
That he has killed
4 innocent people.

33:56.000 --> 33:58.100
Now, why don't we
just do the grid search ? 

33:58.100 --> 33:59.200
If you set up
a grid search

33:59.200 --> 34:00.800
And he confronts
one of your men,

34:00.800 --> 34:02.100
You'll be planning a funeral.

34:03.300 --> 34:05.500
I can guarantee you we're
right about his profile.

34:05.500 --> 34:06.600
This man wants to get rescued.

34:06.600 --> 34:09.400
All i'm asking is that you just
give us a chance to bring him in.

34:12.699 --> 34:13.900
It's channel 11.

34:14.400 --> 34:15.400
Are you ready Garcia ? 

34:15.400 --> 34:17.900
I've got nat recon
satellites all over the ward.

34:19.699 --> 34:20.600
Stand by.

34:22.699 --> 34:24.900
This is John Doe
looking for mark rippen.

34:27.400 --> 34:28.500
Can you help us ? 

34:29.500 --> 34:31.199
You know how to do this
better than we do.

34:34.100 --> 34:36.199
Roger that.
This is number 11, all clear.

34:36.699 --> 34:39.199
Maxey, boy, am I happy
to hear from you.

34:39.300 --> 34:40.600
I'm taking heavy fire.

34:40.600 --> 34:42.400
Request immediate extraction.

34:42.699 --> 34:44.000
What are your coordinates ? 

34:44.000 --> 34:47.300
Unknown. I lost my land
navigational aids.

34:47.699 --> 34:50.699
I went high, but i don't
recognize anything.

34:50.800 --> 34:53.100
I don't have a fix
on my grid coordinates.

34:53.100 --> 34:55.199
Any other way for him
to signal his location ? 

34:56.000 --> 34:57.600
Did you put up any flags ? 

34:57.900 --> 35:00.100
Yeah, you bet
your ass I did.

35:00.100 --> 35:01.700
I'm holding cover here.

35:02.300 --> 35:03.700
Roger that.
Hold your position.

35:05.800 --> 35:09.400
He triangulated. We need to look
for 3 large, colored flags,

35:09.800 --> 35:11.000
Maybe on rooftops.

35:11.000 --> 35:13.400
They'll be identical
in size and shape.

35:13.400 --> 35:15.100
Did you get that, Garcia ? 
Yeah, I got it.

35:17.600 --> 35:19.700
Number 11,
do you still read me ? 

35:19.700 --> 35:22.100
Garcia.
I'm working as fast as I can.

35:22.100 --> 35:23.400
I can still read you
loud and clear.

35:23.400 --> 35:24.300
Stay put.

35:27.900 --> 35:29.500
I found one.
